rc‚ÜêInitialize jarvis;path;cfg
‚çù AppInitFn: resolves the absolute app config path ($APL_SERVICE_APP_CONFIG
‚çù if set, else config/app.config.json next to this service's own
‚çù APLSource folder via jarvis.CodeSource, never the process working
‚çù directory), loads it with LoadAppConfig, and assigns AppState.RootFolder,
‚çù alongside AppState.FrontendRoot (jarvis.CodeSource,'/../frontend', the
‚çù APLSource sibling that Get's static-asset fallback serves from - not
‚çù canonicalised any more than the config path above is, since real file
‚çù operations resolve the literal '..' segment at the OS level regardless).
‚çù A non-zero return refuses startup on a missing or malformed config,
‚çù distinct from a missing folder, which is a per-request 404. Jarvis calls
‚çù Initialize monadically, passing the live server instance as jarvis so
‚çù CodeSource is available; AppState is deliberately absent from the locals
‚çù list below so the assignment escapes to the enclosing namespace (the
‚çù same one Get is fixed into) rather than vanishing when this function
‚çù returns.
 path‚Üê2 ‚éïNQ'.' 'GetEnvironment' 'APL_SERVICE_APP_CONFIG'
 :If 0‚àä‚ç¥path
     path‚Üêjarvis.CodeSource,'/../config/app.config.json'
 :EndIf
 (rc cfg)‚ÜêLoadAppConfig path
 :If 0=rc
     AppState‚Üê‚éïNS''
     AppState.RootFolder‚Üêcfg.rootFolder
     AppState.FrontendRoot‚Üêjarvis.CodeSource,'/../frontend'
 :EndIf
